Breeding male.description: Breeding male Chestnut-sided Warblers have a yellow crown and white throat that breeding male Bay-breasted Warblers lack.

Nonbreeding female.description: Nonbreeding female Chestnut-sided Warblers have yellow (not white) wingbars, a bright yellow-green cap, and a complete white eyering that Bay-breasted Warblers lack.

Nonbreeding female/immature male.description: Nonbreeding female/immature Blackpoll Warblers have faint streaking on the flanks and white (not buffy) undertail coverts unlike Bay-breasted Warblers.

Adult female/immature male.description: Adult female/immature male Cape May Warblers are brighter yellow below than Bay-breasted Warblers with streaked flanks.

Female/immature.description: Female/immature Blackburnian Warblers are brighter yellow below than Bay-breasted Warblers with streaked flanks and a triangular ear patch.

Adult female.description: Female Pine Warblers have a stouter bill, thinner wingbars, and a yellower throat than nonbreeding/immature Bay-breasted Warblers.

Adult male.description: Male Pine Warblers have a stouter bill, thinner wingbars, and a yellower throat than nonbreeding/immature Bay-breasted Warblers.
